Good 👍 Now we will plan the entire CRM project step-by-step from the very beginning so it becomes very easy to develop in Visual Studio.
I will explain it like a development roadmap.
1️⃣ First – Create the Project
Open Visual Studio
Create new project:
ASP.NET Core Web App (MVC)
Project Name:
CRMSystem
Framework:
.NET 8
Authentication:
None
Click Create.
Your base project is ready.
2️⃣ Install Required Packages
Open Tools → NuGet Package Manager → Manage NuGet Packages
Install:
1️⃣ PostgreSQL connector
Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL
2️⃣ Entity Framework tools
Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools
3️⃣ Entity Framework Design
Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design
These will connect your CRM to PostgreSQL.
3️⃣ Create Project Folder Structure
Inside your project create these folders.
CRMSystem
│
├── Controllers
├── Models
├── Views
├── Data
├── Services
└── ViewModels
Purpose:
Folder	Purpose
Models	Database tables
Controllers	Page logic
Views	UI pages
Data	Database connection
Services	Business logic
ViewModels	Data for UI
4️⃣ Create Database Models (Tables)
Create these 4 models inside Models folder.
User Model
User.cs
Fields:
Id
Name
Email
Password
Role
Roles:
Admin
SalesManager
SalesRep
Customer Model
Customer.cs
Fields:
Id
CustomerName
Company
Email
Phone
Address
Status
CreatedBy
CreatedDate
Contact Model
Contact.cs
Fields:
Id
CustomerId
ContactName
Email
Phone
Position
Interaction Model
Interaction.cs
Fields:
Id
CustomerId
UserId
Notes
InteractionType
FollowUpDate
CreatedDate
Example interaction:
Call
Meeting
Demo
Follow-up
5️⃣ Create Database Context
Inside Data folder
CRMDbContext.cs
Add tables:
DbSet<User>
DbSet<Customer>
DbSet<Contact>
DbSet<Interaction>
This connects your models to PostgreSQL.
6️⃣ Connect Database
Open:
appsettings.json
Add:
"ConnectionStrings": {
 "DefaultConnection": "Host=localhost;Database=crm_db;Username=postgres;Password=yourpassword"
}
